@Node 00 "BlitzASMInclude : Introduction"

  @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

    BlitzASMInclude is only an include file that  you  may  use  with  your  favorite
    assembler (e.g. PhxAss).

    This file is a set of macros and constants converted from Blitz one's.  By  using
    this include and an assembler you will be able to write libraries of commands for
    your lovely BlitzBasic.

    I decided to write it because BlitzBasic assembler is very poor,  not  optimized,
    does  not  support  other  processors  than  the  68000, doesn't know about local
    labels... BlitzBasic is not PhxAss ;-)

  @{b}@{u}See also@{ub}@{uu}

    @{" Installation " link 02}
@EndNode
