@Node 04 "BlitzASMInclude : Usage"

  @{b}@{u}Usage@{ub}@{uu}

    Using macros is more easy than BlitzBasic ;-) :

    Blitz :
        !libheader  {198,0,0,0,0}

        !function   {#long}
            !args   {#long,#byte}
            !libs
            !subs   {_Token,0,0}
        !name       {"Token","(Long,Byte) - Do things ;-)"}

        !libfin

    ASM :
        libheader   198,0,0,0,0

        function    long
            args    long,byte
            libs
            subs    _Token
        name        'Token','(Long,Byte) - Do things ;-)'

    I rather prefer ASM typing ;-)

  @{b}@{u}Note@{ub}@{uu}

    @{i}repargs@{ui} macro has been renamed as @{i}repa@{ui}... you can change it if  you  want  to.  I
    made it only for design reasons ;-)

  @{b}@{uu}Invoking@{ub}@{uu}

    Invoking Blitz system function is easy, because token values are allways the same
    (e.g.  $CF01 to alloc a string).. but to invoke users command is more complicated
    has you need to know the token's  value...  You  will  have  to  investigate  for
    this...

    All the way, invoking users tokens is dangerous, because someone (like me ;-) may
    have changed its libraries numbers, and so token's values are no longer good.

    But if you want to allocate some memory, string... It is very easy..

      o You can use ALibJsr.. as usual

        MOVE.L  #Size,D0
        MOVE.L  #Flags,D1
        ALibJsr Blitz_AllocMem

        MOVE.L  D0,A1
        MOVE.L  #Size,D0
        ALibJsr Blitz_FreeMem

      o You can also use my custom macros...

        BAllocMem #Size,#Flags
        BFreeMem  D0,#Size
@EndNode

